    <h1>Revenue referrer order</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Customers &gt; Edit customers &gt; Tab: Statistics → Type of statistic: Revenue by order referrer</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you have carried out changes, entered data or changed settings, click on the save icon in order to save your configuration before leaving the area.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_info_revenue_by_order_referrer">1. Info: revenue by order referrer</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This statistic shows how much <strong>revenue</strong> was generated by each sales order <strong>referrer</strong>. Furthermore, it shows which <strong>percentage</strong> of the total revenue each referrer generated. The data relates to one specific customer. As an alternative to selecting a certain predefined time span, you can also choose an individual <strong>start</strong> and <strong>end date</strong>. Default setting for the <strong>time span</strong>: the <strong>last 30 days</strong>. Default setting of the <strong>status section</strong>: From <strong>status 1</strong> to <strong>status 7</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_details_about_the_statistic">2. Details about the statistic</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> that was generated by the customer will be displayed for each <strong>sales order referrer</strong> within the selected <strong>time span</strong>. If a sales order referrer did not generate any revenue, then this referrer will not be displayed. The <strong>sales order referrer</strong>, the corresponding <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> and the <strong>percentage of total revenue</strong> will be displayed as <strong>information in a mouseover</strong> (see image 1). In this statistic you can see, e.g. how much revenue the customer generated with each referrer.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Show details (mouseover)</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Point your <strong>cursor</strong> at one of the elements in the statistic in order to see <strong>details</strong> about that particular element.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In image 1, you can see that <strong>sales orders coming from the webshop</strong> generated a <strong>revenue</strong> of <strong>12,132.05 Euros</strong>. Furthermore, you can see that this is <strong>79.94 percent</strong> of the total revenue that was generated by all referrers.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
